<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Secretary of State to the
                            Embassy in Italy</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1948v01p1</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d124</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">124</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1948-03-23T13:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1948-03-23T13:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-03-23T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-03-23T13:00:00-05:00" n="124" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d124">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.AA/3–2548: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Italy</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-03-23T13:00:00-05:00">March 25, 1948—1 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>826. For the Ambassador. As you know, Dept has proposed US, UK and France request
                    Security Council reconsider Ital application <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>
                    membership in light <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> favorable recommendation.
                    Brit <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> feels, however, gesture at this
                    time might detract from effectiveness Trieste declaration and could in any event
                    be met by Communist counter propaganda to effect USSR favored admission Italy
                    and Balkans, but Western powers blocking Soviet desires.</p>
                <p>Dept urgently desires your views in light present Ital situation, as well as any
                    informal Ital reaction you may have.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
